cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning scheme with a selective attention mechanism for multimodal wearable sensor data classification. This involves the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI) to deal with complex situations dynamically. The application domains of the proposed approach include healthcare and entertainment, which fall under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning suggests a neural network approach (cs.NE).
